"REV", "(C) 2001", "KEYSPAN", "RICHMOND, CA", and "USA" is silkscreened on the component side of the board. :"0PB4-0123-A" is silkscreened on the bottom of the board. ::"UH154B-AKS-31" and "A2LJ064008701AA" is printed on a label affixed to the bottom. :::Probable '''Aten''' model UH-154B / UH-154B-AKS
The model for this device appears to be UHM-4SL.
The release of this device is presumed to have been in 2001.
The manufacturer of this device is presumed to be '''Aten''' as a similarly named product ([http://www.aten-usa.com/partner.php?product&cat=277&Item=UH154 UH-154]), [http://www.deltaco.se/support/infoSE//uh-154.pdf with essentially the same appearance], was manufactured by the company.
